<Layout title='Plasterers & Painters in Beaconsfield | Hancock' description='Plastering and painting in Beaconsfield. Fixed-price quotes from City & Guilds certified contractors covering Beaconsfield and the surrounding area.' activePage='areas'>
<section style="position:relative;height:340px;display:flex;align-items:flex-end;">
  <div style="position:absolute;top:0;left:0;right:0;bottom:0;background-image:url('/uploads/Hancock-plastering-and-painting%20(1).webp');background-size:cover;background-position:center 30%;"></div>
  <div style="position:absolute;top:0;left:0;right:0;bottom:0;background:linear-gradient(to top,rgba(15,23,42,0.9) 0%,rgba(15,23,42,0.45) 60%,rgba(15,23,42,0.15) 100%);"></div>
  <div style="position:relative;z-index:1;max-width:1280px;margin:0 auto;padding:0 24px 48px;width:100%;box-sizing:border-box;">
    <p style="font-size:12px;color:rgba(255,255,255,0.55);margin:0 0 12px;"><a href="/" style="color:rgba(255,255,255,0.55);text-decoration:none;">Home</a> / <a href="/areas" style="color:rgba(255,255,255,0.55);text-decoration:none;">Areas</a> / Beaconsfield</p>
    <h1 style="font-family:'Lexend',sans-serif;font-size:clamp(30px,5vw,52px);font-weight:700;color:#ffffff;margin:0 0 10px;letter-spacing:-0.04em;line-height:1.05;">Plasterer in Beaconsfield</h1>
    <p style="font-size:16px;color:rgba(255,255,255,0.75);margin:0;">HP9 · Premium plastering &amp; decorating for Beaconsfield's Old and New Town properties.</p>
  </div>
</section>
<section style="padding:56px 24px;background:#ffffff;border-bottom:1px solid #E2E8F0;">
  <div style="max-width:1280px;margin:0 auto;">
    <p style="font-size:12px;font-weight:600;color:#0C7BA8;letter-spacing:0.1em;text-transform:uppercase;margin:0 0 12px;">About Beaconsfield</p>
    <h2 style="font-family:'Lexend',sans-serif;font-size:clamp(20px,3vw,30px);font-weight:600;color:#0F172A;margin:0 0 18px;letter-spacing:-0.03em;line-height:1.2;">Old Town has genuine Georgian and Victorian character; New Town brings mid-century executive residential.</h2>
    <p style="font-size:15px;color:#334155;line-height:1.75;margin:0 0 14px;">Beaconsfield's Old Town is a conservation area with listed buildings, Georgian inns, and Victorian residential streets. The New Town — developed from the 1920s onward — has a high concentration of executive detached housing. Both generate distinct types of plastering and decorating work.</p>
    <p style="font-size:15px;color:#334155;line-height:1.75;margin:0;">Venetian plastering and sash window painting feature on Old Town properties. Renovation plastering, skimming, and quality interior decoration are the recurring jobs in New Town. Beaconsfield is at the outer edge of the service corridor — we cover it and surrounding villages on planned runs.</p>
  </div>
</section>
<section style="padding:56px 24px;background:#F8FAFC;border-bottom:1px solid #E2E8F0;">
  <div style="max-width:1280px;margin:0 auto;">
    <p style="font-size:12px;font-weight:600;color:#0C7BA8;letter-spacing:0.1em;text-transform:uppercase;margin:0 0 12px;">Common problems</p>
    <h2 style="font-family:'Lexend',sans-serif;font-size:clamp(20px,3vw,28px);font-weight:600;color:#0F172A;margin:0 0 28px;letter-spacing:-0.03em;">What goes wrong in Beaconsfield's housing stock.</h2>
    <div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(auto-fit,minmax(240px,1fr));gap:20px;">
      <div style="background:#ffffff;border:1px solid #E2E8F0;border-radius:8px;padding:24px;"><h3 style="font-family:'Lexend',sans-serif;font-size:16px;font-weight:600;color:#0F172A;margin:0 0 8px;">Listed-building fabric in Old Town</h3><p style="font-size:14px;color:#334155;line-height:1.65;margin:0;">The Old Town conservation area has Georgian and listed buildings with lime plaster and historic fabric — work here demands breathable materials and a sympathetic hand.</p></div>
      <div style="background:#ffffff;border:1px solid #E2E8F0;border-radius:8px;padding:24px;"><h3 style="font-family:'Lexend',sans-serif;font-size:16px;font-weight:600;color:#0F172A;margin:0 0 8px;">Premium interior wear</h3><p style="font-size:14px;color:#334155;line-height:1.65;margin:0;">New Town's executive homes carry high-specification interiors where any plaster or polished-plaster repair has to match the existing finish seamlessly.</p></div>
      <div style="background:#ffffff;border:1px solid #E2E8F0;border-radius:8px;padding:24px;"><h3 style="font-family:'Lexend',sans-serif;font-size:16px;font-weight:600;color:#0F172A;margin:0 0 8px;">Sash window upkeep</h3><p style="font-size:14px;color:#334155;line-height:1.65;margin:0;">The Old Town's period properties have original sash windows that need periodic strip, repair, and repainting to stay weathertight.</p></div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
<section style="padding:56px 24px;background:#ffffff;border-bottom:1px solid #E2E8F0;">
  <div style="max-width:1280px;margin:0 auto;">
    <div style="display:flex;gap:64px;flex-wrap:wrap;margin-bottom:48px;">
      <div style="flex:1;min-width:300px;">
        <p style="font-size:12px;font-weight:600;color:#0C7BA8;letter-spacing:0.1em;text-transform:uppercase;margin:0 0 12px;">Neighbourhoods we work in</p>
        <h2 style="font-family:'Lexend',sans-serif;font-size:clamp(20px,3vw,28px);font-weight:600;color:#0F172A;margin:0 0 18px;letter-spacing:-0.03em;line-height:1.2;">Old Town and New Town, two distinct markets.</h2>
        <p style="font-size:15px;color:#334155;line-height:1.75;margin:0 0 14px;"><strong>Beaconsfield Old Town</strong> is a conservation area of Georgian inns, listed buildings, and Victorian residential streets — genuine period fabric requiring careful, traditional work. <strong>New Town</strong>, developed from the 1920s around the station, has a high concentration of executive detached housing. Both generate distinct types of plastering and decorating, and both sit among the most desirable addresses in the corridor.</p>
        <p style="font-size:15px;color:#334155;line-height:1.75;margin:0;">Beaconsfield is at the outer edge of our zone — covered on planned runs.</p>
      </div>
      <div style="flex:1;min-width:300px;">
        <p style="font-size:12px;font-weight:600;color:#0C7BA8;letter-spacing:0.1em;text-transform:uppercase;margin:0 0 12px;">What homeowners ask for</p>
        <h2 style="font-family:'Lexend',sans-serif;font-size:clamp(20px,3vw,28px);font-weight:600;color:#0F172A;margin:0 0 18px;letter-spacing:-0.03em;line-height:1.2;">Period repair and premium finishes.</h2>
        <p style="font-size:15px;color:#334155;line-height:1.75;margin:0 0 14px;">Venetian plastering and sash window painting feature on the Old Town properties; renovation plastering, skimming, and quality interior decoration are the recurring New Town jobs. Exterior render and masonry work is planned for the drier months.</p>
        <p style="font-size:15px;color:#334155;line-height:1.75;margin:0;">A high standard expected, and a fixed price agreed before we start.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <p style="font-size:12px;font-weight:600;color:#0C7BA8;letter-spacing:0.1em;text-transform:uppercase;margin:0 0 24px;">Working in Beaconsfield</p>
    <div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(auto-fit,minmax(220px,1fr));gap:20px;">
      <div><h3 style="font-family:'Lexend',sans-serif;font-size:15px;font-weight:600;color:#0F172A;margin:0 0 8px;">~25 minutes from base</h3><p style="font-size:14px;color:#334155;line-height:1.65;margin:0;">A clear run from Harefield via the A40/M40. At the outer edge of the corridor, covered on planned runs with Gerrards Cross and the Chalfonts.</p></div>
      <div><h3 style="font-family:'Lexend',sans-serif;font-size:15px;font-weight:600;color:#0F172A;margin:0 0 8px;">Conservation-aware</h3><p style="font-size:14px;color:#334155;line-height:1.65;margin:0;">Listed and Old Town properties get breathable, period-appropriate materials and a careful approach. We advise on what's suitable before quoting.</p></div>
      <div><h3 style="font-family:'Lexend',sans-serif;font-size:15px;font-weight:600;color:#0F172A;margin:0 0 8px;">High-spec ready</h3><p style="font-size:14px;color:#334155;line-height:1.65;margin:0;">Venetian plaster and premium finishes for the New Town executive stock — the right materials for the address.</p></div>
      <div><h3 style="font-family:'Lexend',sans-serif;font-size:15px;font-weight:600;color:#0F172A;margin:0 0 8px;">Clean, tidy, insured</h3><p style="font-size:14px;color:#334155;line-height:1.65;margin:0;">Features and surfaces protected, site left immaculate. Fully insured, City &amp; Guilds qualified, no subcontractors.</p></div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
